</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Irish prime minister Albert Reynolds said yesterday that the European
Community could not open negotiations with prospective new members until
agreement is reached on additional aid for poorer EC countries, Reuter
reports from Bonn.
Speaking after talks with Chancellor Helmut Kohl of Germany, he said that
with Europe's highest unemployment rate, Ireland wanted agreement on
increasing the EC's so-called structural funds and creating a new cohesion
fund to help poorer members.
